<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4747206>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 26. (a–g) Rhagasostoma hexagonum Koschinsky; Eocene, Lutetian, Rollgraben near Teisendorf, Bavaria, Germany (a–d) neotype (designated here), SMF 29757; (a) bifurcating branch; (b) autozooid; (c) autozooid opesia with occulusor lamina;(d) avicularium;(e,f) SMF 29754;(e) branch; (f) autozooid opesia; (g) SMF 29755; branch. (h,i) Rhagasostoma circumvallatum Koschinsky; same provenance details as for (a–g); (h) SMF 32077b, autozooids with distinct occlusor laminae; (i) SMF 31915a, autozooids and avicularium. Scale bars: a, e, g = 500 µm; b, d, h = 200 µm; c, f, i = 100 µm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4747206/files/figure.png" .

